>> since
>> they only came on about 3 years of the buses and I think some of the porsche
>> 914 .
> 
> What rubber parts are we talking about?


It is a coupling that connects the fan to the drive pulley for the air pump.
The air pump is driven off the center of the fan through this flexible
coupling. It is made of a bonded rubber and steel part. The rubber is always
separated from the steel, rendering the part useless.


